shared_text:
Phoenix Martial Arts Academy
August 6 at 9:51 PM ·

ATTENTION ALBUQUERQUE & RIO RANCHO PARENTS!!!
We all worry about our children’s health and have concerns about the Pandemic and related closures. To keep up with the current state of the world, Phoenix Martial Arts Academy is excited to announce our DIGITAL LEARNING CAMP of 2020.
Phoenix Martial Arts Academy’s top priority has always been the health and safety for all students. The Digital Learning Camp is perfect for parents who work, require child care, and need an alternative to the traditional classroom.
The Digital Learning Camp offers full-time and hybrid scheduling. The Digital Learning Camp will be instructed and assisted by a Certified Substitute/Teacher. Along with APS required curriculum, students will also get daily physical education and martial arts training.
*Please note that sometimes the school’s schedules may change.

Limited Spots Available.
SIGN UP TODAY!!

post_text:
School is slated to begin on Monday, August 10th. Here’s how you can help your student(s) prepare and practice to become more mindful of health/safety habits for the new school year:

- Get your child a mask. Inexpensive ones are available at Target, Walmart, Old Navy, and many local Facebook markets have individuals selling homemade ones with fun designs.

- Start slow: Have your kiddo wear the mask for 30-45 mins/day, then increase the time to 1-3 hours/day, and so on.

- When they start fidgeting with their masks or getting distracted by them, point it out and help redirect the behavior.

- Encourage sanitary practices. Encourage good health habits. Encourage independence too!

- Staff & teachers will need to start these lessons with their own children too.

We’re all in this together! Let’s continue to strengthen and build a community that’s PROUD TO BE A.S.E!

NewMexicoKidsCAN
May 6 at 3:02 PM ·

📢 A N N O U N C E M E N T 📢

New Mexico is one of 14 states approved to participate in the new Pandemic EBT program. This means 245,000 New Mexico children are now eligible for benefits to make up for meals they would have normally received at school.

We are grateful for the partnership and collaboration of organizations like The Education Trust, Policy Innovators in Education (PIE) Network, and New Mexico Public Education Department for helping advocate for and implement this program.

Learn more: https://nmkidscan.org/blog/new-mexico-approved-for-pandemic-ebt-program/

Stumped on what you can do for a video or photo submission to Staff Appreciation Week?
Here are some fun ideas:
- Tell a silly (and appropriate) joke to make our staff LOL
- Describe or draw a favorite classroom memory or favorite lesson from the school year

- Dress up like your teacher
- Tell us why you're grateful for our staff

- Dance it out

post_text:
Happy Administrative Professionals Day to our front office team, Karen, Alyssa, and Daniella! They not only answer the phones and the door (usually at the same time), but they also answer everyone's questions. (So. Many. Questions.)
These ladies not only know our students, but they also know the families behind our students. They greet students no matter what time they arrive. They deliver forgotten homework, lunch bags, glasses, PE clothes, etc. They help call parents and keep sick kiddos company while waiting for a parent pick up. Currently, they're all elbow-deep conducting next year's registration project remotely and electronically!
Our school wouldn't work without them and they are often the unsung heroes behind our great success.
Karen, Alyssa, & Daniella, we're so lucky to have you and we graciously thank you for all you do for us!

Yearbooks, School Photos, Items in Lockers/Cubbies:
Personal Items: ASE is following the stay-at-home order issued by the state. At this time, we are not allowing students or parents to retrieve any personal items left at the school. If/when the order is lifted and state officials agree, we will announce specific office hours/times for personal item retrieval.
School Photos: Pictures will be mailed to the school. If/when state officials lift stay-at-home order, we will announce specific office hours to pick up photos. Otherwise, the photos will be mailed to the address on file if they are not picked up.
Yearbooks: Yearbooks will be mailed to the school. If/when state officials lift the stay-at-home order, we will announce specific office hours to pick up yearbooks. We may be able to mail these directly to households, but if not, they will be available during our anticipated summer hours or when school restarts in August.
Please email any questions to info@abqse.org

Hopefully you didn’t actually find your photo hidden in these gems! 😂

FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS REGARDING EXTENDED SCHOOL CLOSURE

Today Governor Michelle Lujan Grisham
will sign an Executive Order to direct New Mexico public education to shift to a learn-at-home model as schools remain closed for the rest of the academic year. This decision, which was made in consultation with the New Mexico Public Education Department and the New Mexico Department of Health, is part of a two-pronged plan to protect New Mexicans from COVID-19 and ensure that children are protected, fed and educated and that families are supported through this crisis.

The Public Education Department has put together this document with support from the Early Childhood Education and Care Department and the Children, Youth and Families Department to answer some of your most frequently asked questions. https://bit.ly/2vSIZBQ

post_text:
Dear ASE Families,

ASE follows the schedule for APS regarding weather related school delays/closings. For example, if ALL APS schools are closed due to weather, then ASE is closed. If ALL APS schools are on a 2 hour-delay, then ASE is on a 2 hour delay. The only exception would be Fridays due to our shortened schedule: If all APS schools are on a two hour weather delay on a Friday, then ASE is closed.

Delay/Closing information will be posted on the school website, school social media accounts, and with local new stations (KOAT-7, KOB-4, KRQE-13).

Thank you,

ASE Administration

From our awesome 6th grade science teacher: "Today, I got to observe my students present their models of either plant or animal cells. They all did amazing jobs and I’m so blessed to be their teacher. We had awesome Styrofoam models, edible cake models, and a very creative turtle shaped animal cell. I love how they are able to turn my challenges into a reality and have fun doing so! "
Thank you Ms. Aggad!
